{"id":"data-handling-6","label":"Data Handling - 6","list":[{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"fav-sport","label":"Raw Data: Favourite Sport","data":{"title":"Naresh and Navya collected the favourite game of all students in their class. The below image is the collected data.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/raw-data.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"How many students participated in the survey?","type":"number","value":31},{"qText":"Which game is picked by many as their favourite?","options":"Hockey, Cricket, Kabaddi, Badminton"},{"qText":"Which is the least favourite game?","options":"Badminton, Hockey, Cricket, Kabaddi"},{"qText":"How many students mentioned Hockey as their favourite game?","type":"number","value":8},{"qText":"How many students mentioned Cricket as their favourite game?","type":"number","value":6}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"fav-sweet","label":"Tally Chart : Favourite Sweet","data":{"title":"The teacher decided to bring sweets to the class to celebrate the new year. He collected the choices of the children.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/tally.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"How many students chose jalebi?","type":"number","value":6},{"qText":"Barfi was chosen by _____ students?","type":"number","value":3},{"qText":"How many students chose Gujiya?","type":"number","value":13},{"qText":"Rasgulla was chosen by ______ students?","type":"number","value":7},{"qText":"How many students chose gulab jamun?","type":"number","value":9},{"qText":"What is the total number of students?","type":"number","value":38},{"qText":"Which is the most favourite sweet?","options":"Gujiya, Jalebi, Gulab jamun , Barfi"},{"qText":"Which is the least favourite sweet?","options":"Barfi, Rasgulla, Jalebi, Gulab jamun"}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"shoe-size","label":"Raw Data: Shoe Size","data":{"title":"Sandhya asked her students about the sizes of the shoes they wear. She noted the data on the board. ","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/raw-data-2.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"The largest shoe size in the class is ____.","type":"number","value":7},{"qText":"The smallest shoe size in the class is ____.","type":"number","value":3},{"qText":"There are _________ students who wear shoe size 5.","type":"number","value":10},{"qText":"There are _________ students who wear shoe sizes larger than 4. ","type":"number","value":15},{"qText":"What is the top two sizes that majority of the children have?","options":"4 & 5, 3 & 5, 3 & 4, 5 & 6"}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"transport","label":"Pictograph : Mode of Transport","data":{"title":"The different modes of travel used by the students is given below.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/pictograph.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"Which mode of travel is used by the most number of students? ","options":"School bus, Public bus, Cycle, Walking"},{"qText":"Which mode of travel is used by the least number of students? ","options":"Cycle, School bus, Private car, Walking"},{"qText":"How many students come by the school bus?","type":"number","value":11},{"qText":"How many students come walking or by cycle?","type":"number","value":10},{"qText":"How many students come by either school or private bus?","type":"number","value":16}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"sleep","label":"Pictograph : Hours of Sleep","data":{"title":"Nand Kishor collected responses from the children of his middle school in Berasia regarding how often they slept at least 9 hours during the night. He prepared a pictograph from the data:","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/pictograph-2.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"What is the number of children who always slept at least 9 hours at night? ","type":"number","value":50},{"qText":"How many children sometimes slept at least 9 hours at night?","type":"number","value":25},{"qText":"How many children always slept less than 9 hours each night?","type":"number","value":40}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"library","label":"Pictograph : Library","data":{"title":"The following pictograph shows the number of books borrowed by students, in a week, from the library.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/pictograph-3.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"On which day were the minimum number of books borrowed?","options":"Thursday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday"},{"qText":"What was the total number of books borrowed during the week?","type":"number","value":24},{"qText":"On which day were the maximum number of books borrowed? ","options":"Saturday, Monday, Tuesday, Friday"},{"qText":"How many books were borrowed on Friday and Saturday?","type":"number","value":13}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"absent","label":"Bar Chart : No. of Absentees","data":{"title":"The school clerk collected the number of students absent in each class, and represented the data in a bar chart.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/barchart.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"In Class 2, _______ students were absent that day.","type":"number","value":5},{"qText":"In which class were the maximum number of students absent?","options":"Class 8, Class 3, Class 7, Class 5"},{"qText":"Which class had full attendance that day?","options":"Class 5, Class 4, Class 6, Class 1"},{"qText":"How many students were absent in total?","type":"number","value":27}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"road-traffic","label":"Bar Chart : Road Traffic","data":{"title":"The number of cars passing through the crossing each hour (from 6 a.m.) on a busy road was recorded by a traffic police.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/barchart-2.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"How many total cars passed through the crossing between 6 a.m. and noon?","type":"number","value":4450},{"qText":"In which of the below time range, most vehicles passed?","options":"7 - 9 a.m. , 6 - 8 a.m., 8 - 10 a.m., 10 - 12 noon"},{"qText":"How many cars passed between 10 am to 12 noon? ","type":"number","value":1300},{"qText":"Which of the following is the best time to travel without traffic?","options":"6:45 a.m. , 7:30 a.m., 10:15 a.m., 11:45 a.m."}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"Population","label":"Bar Chart : Population in India","data":{"title":"This bar graph shows the population of India in each decade over a period of 50 years.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/barchart-3.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"What is the increase in population in 2001, when compared to 1991? (in Crores)","type":"number","value":18},{"qText":"Going by the pattern, what do you think about population in 2011? ","options":"It increases, It decreases, Difficult to predict"},{"qText":"What is the increase in population in 1981, when compared to 1951? (in Crores)","type":"number","value":32}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"tractors","label":"Pictograph : Number of Tractors","data":{"title":"The following pictograph shows the number of tractors in five different villages.","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/pictograph-4.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"Which village has the smallest number of tractors?","options":"Village D, Village C, Village B, Village A"},{"qText":"Which village has the most tractors?","options":"Village C, Village E, Village B, Village A"},{"qText":"How many more tractors does Village C have than Village B?","type":"number","value":3},{"qText":"Komal says, “Village D has half the number of tractors as Village E.” Is she right?","options":"Right, Wrong"}]}},{"type":"informationProcessing","id":"girl-students","label":"Pictograph : Number of Girl Students","data":{"title":"The number of girl students in each class of a school is depicted by the pictograph:","type":"image","image":"math/big/data-handling-6/pictograph-5.jpg","questions":[{"qText":"Which class has the least number of girl students?","options":"Class 8, Class 4, Class 5, Class 7"},{"qText":"What is the difference between the number of girls in Classs 5 and 6?","type":"number","value":6},{"qText":"If two more girls were admitted in Class 2, how many girls will be there in the class?","type":"number","value":20},{"qText":"How many girls are there in Class 7?","type":"number","value":12}]}}]}